# Automatic Changelog

The live changelog is automatically generated from Git commits using GitHub Actions.

Each entry contains information such as:

- Commit Title
- Commit Description
- Commit Hash
- Commit URL
- Repository
- Branch
- Author
- Changed Files
- Files Changed Count
- Lines Added
- Lines Removed
- Commit Timestamp
- Release Notes
- Development History

The generated data powers the SmartGen Docs website and provides a searchable development timeline.

---

# Release History

Every tagged release will appear here automatically.

Example:

```text
v1.0.0
v1.1.0
v1.2.0
v2.0.0
```

